narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Definitely. It's a great painting class to take after you've had some introduction to painting. Not as intense as some other classes. If you want to paint for fun, take it!

I would say this course is largely an open studio for artists with technical skill to enjoy painting and develop their own styles. I would recommend this class to a student who has painted a lot before and who wants to work on plein air painting. It is a very open class, so there is not much direction or technical guidance. This may be difficult for a student who doesn't have much painting experience.

I would absolutely recommend Painting Time. It's a wonderful way to really work with oil paints (though I believe you can use acrylic if you want) in a number of special places; we painted YSO practicing, Commons after-hours, and from the penthouse of the Study. It was a really special experience, and I would recommend it to anyone willing to put in the effort.
